title: Carragana
content:
Carragana is a hamlet in Porcupine Rural Municipality No. 395, Saskatchewan, Canada. The community had a population of 30 in 2001. It previously held the status of village until March 25, 1998. The hamlet is located 12 km east of the Town of Porcupine Plain at the intersection of Highway 23 and Highway 678.

Prior to March 25, 1998, Carragana was incorporated as a village, and was restructured as a hamlet under the jurisdiction of the Rural municipality of Porcupine that date.[1]
